1
00:00:05,161 --> 00:00:06,579
The devotee is praying,

2
00:00:06,579 --> 00:00:11,207
“I may forget You at that time, 
but please, don’t forget me.”

3
00:00:11,207 --> 00:00:13,253
That’s also a possibility.

4
00:00:13,733 --> 00:00:17,357
[Basis of the Next Life]

5
00:00:17,828 --> 00:00:23,158
Well, two things ... They’re obsessed 
in meditating in a particular way,

6
00:00:23,305 --> 00:00:27,305
It’s mentioned there, 
in terms of the transition,

7
00:00:27,339 --> 00:00:31,257
like a catepillar. It ...

8
00:00:31,257 --> 00:00:33,735
You know the movements 
of a caterpillar?

9
00:00:33,735 --> 00:00:37,033
It’s on one leaf. 
And here is another leaf.

10
00:00:37,033 --> 00:00:40,098
And it puts part of itself 
on the next leaf.

11
00:00:40,098 --> 00:00:44,331
And then, when it is situated there, 
it pulls the rest of its body into that ...

12
00:00:44,331 --> 00:00:46,661
onto the leaf.

13
00:00:46,661 --> 00:00:49,121
It’s something like that.

14
00:00:49,121 --> 00:00:52,517
Transiting from one life form 
to another.

15
00:00:52,517 --> 00:00:56,787
Many things are mentioned.

16
00:00:56,787 --> 00:01:03,887
But it is not like on the basis 
of the technicality

17
00:01:04,150 --> 00:01:07,101
that everything will be ruined.

18
00:01:07,101 --> 00:01:12,242
But rather Guru Maharaj supported 
the idea your “life-long culture”.

19
00:01:12,242 --> 00:01:17,453
When we say ‘bhāva’, that word 
is best translated as ‘heart’.

20
00:01:17,520 --> 00:01:24,704
The sort of heart that you’ve evolved 
and developed over time

21
00:01:24,704 --> 00:01:29,374
will provide the basis 
for your next life.

